# Implementation Plan - Data Integrity and Telemetry Resolution

This plan resolves the user identity mismatch, UNKNOWN card headers, and false-positive mobile degradation telemetry warnings on the NGO operations dashboard.

## User Review Required

> [!NOTE]
> All changes are strictly confined to the Next.js NGO operations dashboard (`crisis_nexus_ngo/`) and preserve the existing Firestore schemas and backend severity fusion logic.

## Proposed Changes

---

### Identity and Normalizer Layer

#### [MODIFY] [displayUtils.ts](file:///c:/Users/ahash/Downloads/crio-research-v/crisis_nexus_ngo/lib/displayUtils.ts)
* **Email Resolution Robustness:** Update `normalizeDisplayCrisis` (line 124) so that `reporterEmail` prioritizes dynamic `profileData` first:
  ```typescript
  const reporterEmail: string = profileData?.email || profileData?.profile?.email || citizenInput.userEmail || crisis.userEmail || "";
  ```
* **Identity Resolution Robustness:** Robustify `resolveCitizenIdentity` fallback pipeline to include `profileData?.email` and `profileData?.profile?.email` immediately after name options to ensure a fallback to their registered email before falling back to legacy input or UID strings.

